Class for containing a restriction object subtrees in NameConstraints. See
RFC 3280.



      GeneralSubtree ::= SEQUENCE
      {
        baseName                    GeneralName,
        minimum         [0]     BaseDistance DEFAULT 0,
        maximum         [1]     BaseDistance OPTIONAL
      }


@see LibOrg.BouncyCastle.asn1.x509.NameConstraints

Constructor from a given details.
According RFC 3280, the minimum and maximum fields are not used with any name forms, thus minimum MUST be zero, and maximum MUST be absent.
If minimum is null, zero is assumed, if maximum is null, maximum is absent.
