Calculate the numbers u1, u2, and u3 such that:

u1 * a + u2 * b = u3

where u3 is the greatest common divider of a and b.
a and b using the extended Euclid algorithm (refer p. 323
of The Art of Computer Programming vol 2, 2nd ed).
